messages.text: Well, this is awkward ‚Äî when a dating app pairs you with‚Ä¶
Your ex.
I did NOT mean to swipe right on you. I don‚Äôt know what happened!

The dating app gods are at work.
Haha, maybe. So how are you? I mean‚Ä¶since‚Ä¶
Since my soulmate walked out of my life nearly a year ago?
Cal, I‚Äôm sorry. Ugh.
It‚Äôs okay. I‚Äôm good, actually. Doing the usual‚Ä¶
Saving kids with cancer?
Trying üôÇ How are you? How‚Äôs San Francisco?
Foggy. And all the guys here have mega beards and dress like they‚Äôre in a barber shop quartet.

I thought that was Brooklyn. Speaking of‚Ä¶how‚Äôs NYC?
I wouldn‚Äôt know. I moved a few months ago.
I‚Äôm heading up the pediatrics department at St. Mary‚Äôs Hospital in SF.

Why didn‚Äôt you hit me up when you got here?
Because you broke up with me?
Oh, yeah. Right. I‚Äôm a jerk.
Nah, I get it‚Äî
You‚Äôre just a free-love, won‚Äôt settle now or maybe ever type. You‚Äôre an independent soul.
That‚Äôs why I didn‚Äôt contact you ‚Äî because I was respecting your wishes.
But I think we crushed your dad‚Äôs dream of us getting back together üòä
He still texts me, btw.
Sorry about that.
Don‚Äôt be sorry. Your dad‚Äôs awesome, haha.
When I moved, I flew through Chicago. He took me out to dinner.

But I love your dad! He‚Äôs the best. And you know I don‚Äôt mind that he semi-adopted me when my dad died.

Well, I mean, you did. But, that‚Äôs okay ‚Äî they‚Äôre not mistakes if you learn from them.
Uh-oh, you‚Äôre starting to sound like my dad too‚Ä¶
Next, you‚Äôll be saying you‚Äôre #Blessed.
Oh, I‚Äôm clearly #Blessed. I make a good salary at St. Mary‚Äôs‚Äî
AND they cover my membership at the gym next door to the hospital.

So, I decided to get back in shape. Selena helped me.
Selena?
Only the best personal trainer ever.
Cal sends her picture of very sexy, scantily clad trainer.
Wow. She‚Äôs‚Ä¶in shape. Geez.
She‚Äôs very dedicated to her work, thankfully‚Äî

Oh, I was gonna say‚Ä¶you look fantastic in your profile pic! Good for you.
You‚Äôve got a lot of muscles.
They‚Äôre easier to see now that there isn‚Äôt so much fat.
You were never fat!
Just a big boned man who loves Doritos. You have a great pic too‚Äî
I like the new hair. Blond looks great on you.
I always said you were the most beautiful girl in the world, and you keep proving me right üôÇ
And you being the nicest ex-boyfriend in the world makes me feel terrible. Is that the plan?
Is it working?
Sort of.
Wanna hear a weird coincidence?
Sure.
Last time I was home, Dad showed me a binder that had HIS wedding plans for us in it.
How ridiculous is that? I can‚Äôt believe he presumed so much!
I don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs ridiculous. I mean, I did seek his blessing to ask you to marry me.

I was going to propose‚Ä¶
Before you‚Ä¶broke up with me and moved to SF.
You WERE?!
I got a ring. Your dad helped me pick it out.
He never told me.
Well, it‚Äôs kind of a moot point now. Besides, who wants to get married?
Who needs to be tied down to one person forever, right?
Did I say that?
You did and you were totally right. You‚Ä¶and Selena changed my mind.

Dating is a label, and I‚Äôm not sure I believe in labels anymore‚Ä¶
Anyway, it‚Äôs just a casual thing. No strings. No commitment.

She‚Äôs‚Ä¶gorgeous. Like, model-gorgeous.

Yes?
Maybe we should grab a pizza?

How many girls are you‚Ä¶wait, never mind. I don‚Äôt want to know.
